%S A395813 1,3,60,3348,368064,67003200,18231609600,6930445536000,
%T A395813 3507873984921600,2280708946859212800,1852343728078233600000,
%U A395813 1837871326852962508800000,2187422284721328635904000000,3075950132516829382675660800000,5045182380712847160087242342400000
%N A395813 Number of perfect matchings in the complete 4-partite graph K_{n,n,n,n}.
%C A395813 a(n) is the number of ways to partition 4 groups of n labeled points into 2n pairs such that no pair lies within a single group.
%C A395813 Equivalently, a(n) is the number of ways to pair up the 4n unit boundary segments of an n X n square so that no two segments on the same side are paired with each other.
%C A395813 The number of perfect matchings of the complete multipartite graph K_{n_1,...,n_r} equals E[Product_i He_{n_i}(X)] with X a standard normal random variable, where He is the probabilist's Hermite polynomials (see Azor, Gillis, Victor). Here a(n) = E[He_n(X)^4].
%D A395813 R. Azor, J. Gillis and J. Victor, Combinatorial applications of Hermite polynomials, SIAM Journal on Mathematical Analysis, 13 (1982), 879-890.
%H A395813 Meghanto Majumder, <a href="/A395813/b395813.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..210</a>
%H A395813 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CompleteMultipartiteGraph.html">Complete Multipartite Graph</a>
%H A395813 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/PerfectMatching.html">Perfect Matching</a>
%F A395813 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} (k!*binomial(n,k)^2)^2 * (2*n-2*k)!.
%F A395813 a(n) = (10*n^2 - 10*n + 3)*a(n-1) - 9*(n-1)^4*a(n-2) for n >= 2.
%F A395813 a(n) = (2*Pi)^(-1/2) * Integral_{x=-oo..oo} He_n(x)^4 * exp(-x^2/2) dx, where He_n is the probabilists' Hermite polynomial.
%F A395813 a(n) = Sum_{k1,k2,k3,k4 >= 0} (-1)^(k1+k2+k3+k4) * (Product_{i=1..4} n!/(k_i! * 2^k_i * (n-2*k_i)!)) * (4*n - 2*(k1+k2+k3+k4) - 1)!! (inclusion-exclusion over pairs within a group).
%e A395813 a(1) = 3: K_{1,1,1,1} = K_4 has 3 perfect matchings.
%e A395813 a(2) = 60: of the 7!! = 105 pairings of 8 points in 4 groups of 2, exactly 60 avoid all intra-group pairs.
%t A395813 a[n_] := Sum[(k!*Binomial[n, k]^2)^2*(2*n - 2*k)!, {k, 0, n}]; Array[a, 15, 0]
%o A395813 (PARI) a(n) = sum(k=0, n, (k!*binomial(n, k)^2)^2*(2*n-2*k)!);
%o A395813 (Python)
%o A395813 from math import comb, factorial
%o A395813 def a(n): return sum((factorial(k)*comb(n, k)**2)**2 * factorial(2*(n-k)) for k in range(n+1))
%Y A395813 Cf. A101485 (perfect matchings of K_{4n}), A000142 (perfect matchings of K_{n,n}), A002720 (matchings of K_{n,n}), A293075 (matchings of K_{n,n,n}), A297487 (maximal matchings of K_{n,n,n}), A395815 (perfect matchings of K_{2n,2n,2n}).
%K A395813 nonn,easy,new
